Greater Rune: This rune symbolizes ill intent, lasting suffering, and misfortune. It is commonly known as the rune of curses, allowing those who wield it the ability to inflict calamity upon their foes. Requires having used the Help action to help a hostile creature a minimum of DAMAGE1-5DAMAGE times while in active combat to attune.SPACESPACEWhile wearing or using an item imbued with this rune, you gain the following feature.SPACESPACECurse of RegretSPACEAs an action, you attempt to curse a target within DISTANCE15-30DISTANCE feet of you with terrible regret. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be cursed for TIME2-4TIME rounds. For the duration, whenever the target makes an attack against a creature they must take the Help action as a bonus action, helping the creature they targeted. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACEYou may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 3 runic attunement slots. ADDEND Lesser - remove You may invoke this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest. This rune occupies 2 runic attunement slots. ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - remove A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours. ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - remove A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours. ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - add While a creature is poisoned as a result of a runic ability, that creature has disadvantage on Constitution saving throws and Concentration checks to maintain a spell ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - distance 15 ADDEND ADDEND Lesser - time 1 ADDEND 
